title: Crash when user taps sign in twice on recover screen
body:
### Description

*Type*: Bug

*Summary*: When i am on recover screen and tap Sign in twice after i entered my pass phrase and password - app crashes (looks like that from user POV). When i checked logs i have noticed that node is not running.


#### Actual behavior
```
00:07 I/hwaps: JNI_OnLoad
00:07 V/AudioManager: playSoundEffect   effectType: 0
00:07 D/StatusModule: StartNode result: {"error":""}
00:07 D/StatusModule: Geth node started
00:07 D/ServiceConnector: Sending message to service: 
00:07 D/StatusService: Received service message.{ when=-1ms what=0 target=im.status.ethereum.module.StatusService$IncomingHandler }
00:07 W/libEGL: EGLNativeWindowType 0xcc476008 disconnect failed
00:07 V/InputMethodManager: Reporting focus gain, without startInput
```


TF log https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8574724/sessions/4399877144/?accessToken=c8nAHFN3ZYqOMC0JcMjY-a4/3DA

### Reproduction

- Open Status
- Go to recover
- Enter details and tap sign in twice
FYI, on 0.9.27, when I tap sign in button multiple times the following error appears. Pressing OK dimisses it and all works fine. Tested on iPhone 8, iOS 12

Btw, `00:07 D/StatusModule: StartNode result: {"error":""}` means there is no error and node was successfully started as Igor noticed on [Slack](https://status-im.slack.com/archives/C8KB9DR60/p1537363308000100?thread_ts=1537357520.000100&cid=C8KB9DR60).
